00:10:18.280 --> 00:10:25.159
kind of biased environment, when it's hard, you know why you're doing it. So that is the first

00:10:25.159 --> 00:10:39.719
thing. The second thing is start with first listening. If you want to build trust with people,

00:10:40.679 --> 00:10:47.400
if you want to become a better leader, actually at all levels, especially the higher levels,

00:10:48.280 --> 00:10:50.520
start with working on your listening skills.

00:10:52.119 --> 00:10:58.280
Listen not like, you know, and listening is kind of, there's a big spectrum. There's this

00:10:58.280 --> 00:11:07.159
kind of listening like you're playing on your smartphone. And there's listening where you're

00:11:07.159 --> 00:11:15.799
really, really listening. You're 100% with the other person. You don't multitask. Maybe you take

00:11:15.799 --> 00:11:23.960
notes, but you see the other person. You have full screen or best is actually in person.

00:11:25.719 --> 00:11:32.440
And you really connect. You ask questions. You make follow-up questions. You have eye contact,

00:11:32.440 --> 00:11:40.200
all these different things that will help you to build trust. And that will help you to make

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:48.200
everything easier because the key thing is building trust. Now talking about visibility,

00:11:49.239 --> 00:11:52.039
there's of course visibility within your organization,

00:11:53.239 --> 00:11:58.200
but I think it's even easier to have visibility outside of your organization.

00:11:59.960 --> 00:12:05.640
And from a professional point of view, the number one place where you can build that is LinkedIn.

00:12:05.799 --> 00:12:13.719
